# 3. Critical Decisions & Reasoning History

**Freshness: High - verified in this completion session.**

- Kept the Phase 2 neutral work-app shell and progressive disclosure; Phase 3 did not foreground
  agent machinery or replace Streamlit.
- Made local identity deterministic and loopback-only so the offline demo stays simple without
  making headerless public access look safe.
- Put tenant scope in persistence, repositories, services, analytics, exports, and caches rather
  than relying on UI filters.
- Required asymmetric OIDC tokens and exact issuer matching; bounded JWKS unknown-key refreshes.
- Separated Streamlit OAuth client secrets from backend token verification and required HTTPS before
  forwarding access tokens.
- Used database leases and fencing rather than an in-memory queue; retained ambiguous leases until
  expiry and never claimed exactly-once provider billing.
- Replaced export denylisting with a strict safe-provenance allowlist so future fields fail closed.
- Disabled every generic billable generation retry, including 429, because compatible gateways do
  not prove rejection before upstream work.
- Kept calibration explicitly offline/statistical until a human-reviewed authorized live study.

