# 6. Debugging History & Failure Modes

**Freshness: High - verified in this completion session.**

- Cold subroutes originally collided with Streamlit's adjacent legacy `pages/` discovery; the
  top-level launcher fixes registration rather than hiding an overlay.
- Populated SQLite downgrade initially failed because batch reconstruction dropped a referenced
  parent while foreign keys were active; private migration connection handling and FK validation
  fixed it.
- PostgreSQL exposed host/database clock skew in `next_claim_at`; server-side database defaults and
  an integration assertion fixed immediate claim eligibility.
- Heartbeat failure could close an attempt yet make work immediately replayable; the worker now
  cancels in-flight work, stops writes, closes only the attempt, and leaves the lease until expiry.
- Exact-key export redaction leaked unanticipated content fields; strict allowlisting and a full
  sentinel fixture now make unknown fields disappear.
- Production OIDC could forward a token to plaintext `api_url`; non-test OIDC now requires HTTPS and
  dashboard auth/client use one validated settings snapshot.
- Generic 429 retry could duplicate billed work; provider SDK and adapter retries are both zero.
- Compose static parsing did not catch a missing API-container HTTPS URL; process-health proof did,
  and the shared anchor now supplies it to both services.
- One local Playwright command initially opened the unrelated app already on `8501`; the final proof
  used isolated owned ports and left the other service untouched.

